Recently I found that when I called a method in java whose return type was String and got `null` as a result through luajavabridge, the app crushed. Though I can return an empty string instead of `null`, but it's legal in java to return `null` when return type is String.

I firstly thought that might be a bug in JNI, but finally I fixed it in CCLuaJavaBridge.cpp:
the original code

```
bool LuaJavaBridge::CallInfo::execute(void)
{
...
        case TypeString: {
            m_retjs = (jstring)m_env->CallStaticObjectMethod(m_classID, m_methodID);
            const char *stringBuff = m_env->GetStringUTFChars(m_retjs, 0);
            m_ret.stringValue = new string(stringBuff);
            m_env->ReleaseStringUTFChars(m_retjs, stringBuff);
            break;
        }
...
}
...
int LuaJavaBridge::CallInfo::pushReturnValue(lua_State *L)
{
...
    case TypeString:
      lua_pushstring(L, m_ret.stringValue->c_str());
      return 1;
...
}
```

the code fixed

```
bool LuaJavaBridge::CallInfo::execute(void)
{
...
  case TypeString: {
    m_retjs = (jstring)m_env->CallStaticObjectMethod(m_classID, m_methodID);
    const char *stringBuff = m_env->GetStringUTFChars(m_retjs, 0);
    if(stringBuff != NULL){
        m_ret.stringValue = new string(stringBuff);
    }
    m_env->ReleaseStringUTFChars(m_retjs, stringBuff);
    break;
  }
...
}
...
int LuaJavaBridge::CallInfo::pushReturnValue(lua_State *L)
{
...
    case TypeString:
      if(m_ret.stringValue != NULL){
          lua_pushstring(L, m_ret.stringValue->c_str());
      }else{
          lua_pushnil(L);
      }
      return 1;
...
}
...
```

P.S. function `LuaJavaBridge::CallInfo::executeWithArgs` should be modified as well
